caption: I go to this marvelous  place from time to time  as I love the special air that is exist in this restaurant. The crew is highly friendly and well trained. The service is awfully rapid. Not to mention, the food you eat is good. I visited often and I was always delighted. The price is reasobable. I highly suggest this place to all my friends.

We got to the restaurant for the first seating at 5pm and it was packed within 20 minutes!  A nice clean family style restaurant with a friendly staff.  We tried three different beers, potato pancakes, German ravioli, venison and pork loin entrees.  I would definitely go back to try the different beers and more potato pancakes ~ they were awesome!!!
The hours have not been updated to reflect the pandemic. Call ahead before you show up to closed doors.
Awesome beer and amazing ambiance !

came from out of town for a birthday trip to DC with my bf, turned me away because they didn’t recognize my ID and said it was fake after barely looking at it. threatened to call some ID place and have me locked up. we decided it wasn’t worth it and just left. if you’re coming from out of town be warned lol

Great place to enjoy german and american beer and a small selection of german food (brats and giant pretzels is all that's on the food menu if I recall). The seating area is on the roof and the roof was open to the sky (plenty of ventilation during COVID) when we were there, but there's also walls and plenty of heat vents to keep you warm on cooler nights. I'm definitely coming back!

Other things I will note. It gets super loud even in a midsize crowd. So not super great for conversation amongst large group. You can only hear the person right next to you. Sauf Haus is seemingly always crowded and bustling so it's a great place to spend an afternoon if you like being in the heart of a crowd. The patio on the top most floor is full of German style benches and seems massive thanks to its beautiful open windows on the sides and above (I thought it was open until this last time I went). The beers are decently priced at ~8 for a pint and ~15 for a stein regardless of what beer you get. They also have fruit radlers so it's not all pilsners or wheat beers on tap, which is nice for someone looking for a lighter option. Their only food options are wursts and pretzels, so don't plan to come here for a full meal, but they do hit the spot in their own way.

I liked Saufhaus a lot more when it opened.  The atmosphere remains sort of fun german, but sadly gone is the endearing bavarian themed music.  They also don't use the taller wiezner glass, in favor of steins (I suspect this probably has to do with the fragility of the former.  This does detract from the proper mouthfeel of the beer.  The other grip I have with them is I feel they give too much head when pouring a liter, it cheats you out of beer and makes the beer you have a little less carbonated than it should be.  Overall the beer remains pretty solid, I've generally had good experience with the service.  If you can avoid the bier garden during peak hours I would, it gets way too cramped.

Decent place with a nice authentic, varied German draft beer list (Spaten, Erdinger, Franziskaner, Hofbrau, Maisel's, Weihenstephaner, Radeberger) and one American - Devil's Backbone. 1/2 liter or full liter.  Food is focused on natural sausages (typically on pretzel bun). Current styles are Debreziner (pork, spicy smoked) and Bauernswurst (pork and beef with mustard seeds). On Friday and Saturday they currently offer Beef Brisket Sliders w/ sauerkraut and a potato cake in the form of a fried ball (lol). Platters and a la carte offered. And airways to the House Made spicy mustard, not the stone ground bought offered. It's wonderfully spicy. Over fries, better yet tater tots with that! (come on owners, I know it's not authentic, but profit margin! Lol. You'll want to drink.  Happy Hour now consists of $2 off food that isn't a la carte (essentially platters are discounted).  Decent place. I was in the main 2nd FL. Not a real German Bier Hall ambiance. Rooftop deck is a Rooftop deck, so nice during nice weather.  I've had better German themed food and beer in the area. But I'm not offended by the place, just not running back.
